{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011CfWRsZ5rGB3WvDPUF3Q1e","type":"tool_result","content":"1100\t    `LEFT JOIN (SELECT DISTINCT user_id FROM game_entries)` to avoid the\n1101\t    N×M Cartesian explosion), `player_profiles` (username),\n1102\t    `referral_codes` (code), `referral_earnings` (wager + earnings sums\n1103\t    grouped per referrer), and pending `referral_claims` (sum where status\n1104\t    in pending/processing). Defaults to 50 rows, capped at 250. Sorted by\n1105\t    `referrer_earned_lamports DESC` so the top earners surface first.\n1106\t  - `listKolPerformance({ limit })` — `referral_kol_rates` joined with\n1107\t    matching aggregate subqueries on `referral_links` and\n1108\t    `referral_earnings` so the KOL table renders rate + actual production\n1109\t    side-by-side. Defaults to 100, capped at 500. Sorted by earnings\n1110\t    desc, then `updated_at` desc, then `user_id` asc for stable order.\n1111\t  - `listReferralClaims({ filters, limit })` — filterable claims table with\n1112\t    eight optional filters: `status`, `userId`, `minAmountLamports`,\n1113\t    `maxAmountLamports`, `requestedFrom`, `requestedTo`, `txSignature`,\n1114\t    `errorContains` (ILIKE). The `status='failed'` value widens to\n1115\t    `('failed','error')` so the command-center drill-down link works\n1116\t    without a separate alias contract. Defaults to 100, capped at 500.\n1117\t  - `getReferralGraphNode(userId, { refereeLimit })` — one-hop node\n1118\t    centered on `userId`: inbound referrer (back-link with username +\n1119\t    code) + outbound referees (forward-link, ordered by `created_at`).\n1120\t    Returns `null` for unknown users so the page can render a 404 cleanly.\n1121\t- View-model contracts in `peek/src/lib/types/peek.ts`:\n1122\t  - Added `PeekGrowthOverviewMetricId` union (8 ids),\n1123\t    `PEEK_GROWTH_OVERVIEW_METRIC_IDS` const array, `PeekGrowthOverview`,\n1124\t    `PeekTopReferrerRow`, `PeekKolPerformanceRow`, `PeekGrowthClaimRow`\n1125\t    (extends per-user `PeekReferralClaimRow` with `userId`, `username`,\n1126\t    `wallet` so the table can link rows back to user-detail),\n1127\t    `PeekReferralClaimFilters`, `PeekReferralGraphRefereeRow`,\n1128\t    `PeekReferralGraphInboundReferrer`, `PeekReferralGraphNode`. All\n1129\t    browser-safe; no server imports introduced.\n1130\t- Boundedness + safety:\n1131\t  - Every list query takes a `limit` and clamps it through `clampLimit`\n1132\t    against per-feature `DEFAULT` and `MAX` constants exported from the\n1133\t    module (`PEEK_GROWTH_TOP_REFERRERS_DEFAULT_LIMIT`,\n1134\t    `PEEK_GROWTH_KOL_DEFAULT_LIMIT`,\n1135\t    `PEEK_GROWTH_CLAIMS_DEFAULT_LIMIT`).\n1136\t  - `Promise.all` parallelises the eight overview counts so the metrics\n1137\t    page does not chain queries sequentially.\n1138\t  - Filters are passed as parameterised values (no `unsafe`); `null`\n1139\t    filters are skipped via `(${condition === null} or …)` template\n1140\t    expressions matching the existing `list-peek-users.ts` pattern.\n1141\t- No frontend wiring this iteration — the next two checklist items\n1142\t  (`/growth/referrals` + `/growth/kol` UI, then dedicated tests) handle\n1143\t  page composition and assertion coverage.\n1144\t- Targeted check (peek): `pnpm lint` ✅, `pnpm typecheck` ✅,\n1145\t  `pnpm test` ✅ (196/196, no regressions).\n1146\t## Iteration 27 — 2026-04-25T12:22:12Z — OK\n1147\t- **Log**: iteration-027.log\n1148\t\n1149\t## Iteration 28 — 2026-04-25\n1150\t\n1151\t- FR-7 frontend pages: wired the growth/referral and growth/kol surfaces on\n1152\t  top of iteration 27's queries.\n1153\t  - `peek/app/growth/referrals/page.tsx` — server-rendered route. Loads the\n1154\t    8-metric overview into `MetricStrip`, the top-50 referrer table, and a\n1155\t    URL-addressable claims table. Each section has its own try/catch so a\n1156\t    single broken query doesn't blank the page; errors render through the\n1157\t    component's `error` prop. Calls `getPeekActorContext` and gates the\n1158\t    render with `isRouteAllowedForRole` so a no-role caller sees an\n1159\t    \"access denied\" alert instead of the data shell (the layout still does\n1160\t    the outer gate; this is the page-level belt-and-braces).\n1161\t  - `peek/app/growth/kol/page.tsx` — same shape, just the KOL table.\n1162\t- New components in `peek/src/components/`:\n1163\t  - `growth-referrers-table.tsx` — dense table over `PeekTopReferrerRow`\n1164\t    with a `<Link href=\"/users/{userId}\">` drill-down, monospace wallet,\n1165\t    right-aligned numeric columns, and an inline empty state explaining\n1166\t    that `referral_links` is empty rather than rendering a misleading\n1167\t    zero row.\n1168\t  - `growth-claims-table.tsx` — dense table over `PeekGrowthClaimRow`\n1169\t    using the existing `StatusChip` for status (positive/info/negative\n1170\t    tones); links the user cell to user-detail; renders monospace tx\n1171\t    signatures; collapses null processed_at/error/txSignature to \"—\".\n1172\t  - `growth-kol-table.tsx` — dense table over `PeekKolPerformanceRow`\n1173\t    showing rate_bps, set_by, created/updated, and the joined performance\n1174\t    columns from the engine query.\n1175\t  - `growth-claims-filter-bar.tsx` — `<form action=\"/growth/referrals\">`\n1176\t    with status (select), userId (text), min/max amount (numeric),\n1177\t    requestedFrom/requestedTo (date), txSignature (text), and error\n1178\t    contains (text). All inputs are URL-addressable so an investigation\n1179\t    state can be shared internally.\n1180\t- New URL-param helper: `peek/src/lib/growth-search-params.ts`\n1181\t  (`PEEK_REFERRAL_CLAIM_STATUSES` + `normalizeReferralClaimFiltersFromSearchParams`).\n1182\t  Whitelists the status value against the migration's check constraint so\n1183\t  an unknown `?claimStatus=foo` collapses to `null` rather than passing\n1184\t  through to the engine. Date inputs acce